			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I just got finished with the Elemental Empathy quest at level 53.  I had two friends with me, a level 53 paladin and a level 45 druid.  It does take some time to get it, but in the beginning we made it harder than it had to be.  Do NOT try to fight the luggald inside that little room.  Pull him into the hallway.  There is only one roamer that goes by there and if you kill him before you pull the luggald, you won't have a problem.  To pull the luggald from the room, I had my pet guard near the one way wall and when he faced the wall we knew the luggald had popped.  IF we had killed the roamer (or another group had if they were killing in the hallway), the paladin would be invis'd and swim to the room then pull the luggald into the hallway where we made mince meat of him.
<br />

<br />
When we were trying to fight the luggald inside the room he would always wind up in the water and that just made things way too difficult.
<br />

<br />
The strength of lava does drop off of the luggald reavers too.  I know one of mine dropped from an abomination and one dropped from a reaver and don't remember what the first one I got dropped off of, I think it was an abomination.
<br />

<br />
Using the hallway method made it possible for us to do this without dieing every time or every other time.  Also, you must allow time for this camp.  Just going for one or two rounds a night it will take forever to get it.  Give yourself several hours at least for a camp and you should get at least one to drop.  It does seem to be about one drop in seven luggalds on average.
<br />

<br />
At level 52 and 53 the experience is decent but not great and the money is practically non-existent, so hope you have a couple of good friends or guildmates to help out.  Unfortunately, on Povar the zone was relatively empty every time I was there and no one went farther east to try for the luggald on the stair that was mentioned earlier in the thread and for my little group it would have been suicide to try.
<br />

<br />
Good luck to anyone going after this and I'll certainly be willing to help a fellow mage get their Elemental Empathy spell, just not too soon, I am soo tired of that mine!  :o</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
